    <!--
    TESTING CHECKLIST:
    □ 1. Deploy to sandbox
    □ 2. Create test user
    □ 3. Assign permission set
    □ 4. Verify can create records
    □ 5. Verify can read owned records
    □ 6. Verify can edit owned records
    □ 7. Verify can delete owned records (if applicable)
    □ 8. Verify respects sharing rules (cannot modify others' records)
    □ 9. Verify field permissions work correctly
    □ 10. Verify tab/app visibility
    □ 11. Test reports and API access
    □ 12. Document any issues

    SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS:
    - ViewAllRecords=false ensures users only see records they own or are shared with
    - ModifyAllRecords=false ensures users cannot modify all records
    - ViewAllData=false ensures sharing rules are respected
    - ModifyAllData=false prevents unrestricted data modification
    - EditReadOnlyFields=false prevents editing system/readonly fields

    SHARING RULES:
    This permission set respects org-wide defaults and sharing rules:
    - Users can only access records they own or are shared with
    - Consider pairing with role hierarchy or sharing rules for broader access
    - If territory management is enabled, consider ViewAllData for territory-based access

    BEST PRACTICES:
    - Start restrictive, expand as needed
    - Document business justification for permissions
    - Review quarterly for unused permissions
    - Test with actual users before production
    - Combine with profile permissions (additive model)

    MAINTENANCE:
    - Review new custom fields quarterly
    - Audit usage vs granted permissions
    - Remove unused objects to reduce complexity
    - Update documentation for any changes
    - Track permission set assignments
    -->
</PermissionSet>
